<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Shadow Knight have long been repressed but lately we have increased in power and greatness.  But it isn't until we reach a certain level that we attain that power.  Our Lifetap becomes our greatest asset with a quest spell that drains 280 life from our target.  This compares greatly to the paladins healing ability.  Also what paladin do you know with invisability?  My final agrument as to why SKs are not only equal but better then paladins warriors is our ability to feign death.  At the first sign of trouble we have an escape plan, though it may fail often it works for anything save a god or dragon perhaps.  In the end, SKs are merely an egg waiting to be hatched and that hatching point is level 50.<hr>Kyree ShadowMaster</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
