<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=nazrael&Board=shadow&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Nazrael (nazrael) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Wow, it's so nice to know I only have to wait until level 50 to reach my potential!<p>

Anyway, in case Verant ever reads this and decides to listen, this would be my SK wish list.<p>

1) The obligatory change-the-pet wish: I'm not asking for a stronger, higher hp pet. However, two previously mentioned point do merit bearing out. First, how about giving us a distinct looking pet. I'm thinking something like a shadowed image of ourself. Not as strong obviously, but that would look pretty cool, a second SK made of smoke or shadow or just plain darkness following me around, perhaps with glowing spectral eyes or something. The other point is the fact that we DO have to deal with ever annoying little aggro green con in Norrath because of our pets. How about making them basically undetectable unless they are set to taunt or actually fighting something. I too get tired of having to kill pumas in Oasis. Such a waste of valuable playing time...<p>

2) The equally obligatory make-Harm Touch-stronger wish: I WOULD like to see the power uf this skill increased. Instead of Instant Death, as so many people ask for, why not just make it the true equal of Lay on Hands. Where LH has the potential to fully restore the Paladin's HP, make Harm Touch do damage equal to the SKs max hp. Granted this will make Ogre and Troll HTs considerably stronger than that of a DE or Erudite, but since they are dumber and more likely to be resisted anyway, it should all pretty much even out.<p>

3) Can we get just ONE spell, even at a high level, that will enable us to buy/sell some damn equipment from non-evil merchants? Maybe an Illusion Wussy High Elf spell or something? The trials and tribulations we have to go through for even the most rudimentary purchases (food/water) is ridiculous. I hate having to pay somebody into buying food for me. It certainly doesnt make me feel intimidating or super-evil to have to beg for food. Better yet, since the merchants are always telling me "I thought you Shadow Knights just stole what you wanted!", why not just let us do so! It would be great to be able to come into a shop and strongarm the merchant into giving up the goods.<p>

My 2cp for now. Bear in mind that the thread title IS "Wish List"</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
