<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I play a shadow knight on Brell Serilis.  All things considered, he is very fun to play.  I will continue to play him even if nothing changes about them.  However, I think our HT ability could be better.  I think it should be a life draining attack, instead of an instant death.  It doesn't even need to be a full drain.  I don't think we would be unbalanced at all if we did 600 damage to them while restoring a portion of that to ourselves.  Even if it was just 1 or 2 hundred, every little bit helps.  As far as pets go, they aren't that bad.  Necros need them to keep the npc's off of them.  We are tanks.  We can take a beating.  Our pets are there to do what they can to help us.  /pet taunt off is a great command to know.  It keeps your pet alive a lot longer, which is more damage.  I do think they shouldn't aggro all the greens though.  That isn't too big of a deal though.  You just need to be careful and no what you're doing.  Anyways, those are my thoughts on the class of shadow knights.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
