<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=nagalaz&Board=shadow&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Nagalaz (nagalaz) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Shadowknights have some hideous disadvantageous.  My wishlist doesnt (in my opinion) imbalance the game, but Verant wont enable these modest changes because doing so would be admitting theyve been screwing the dark knights the whole time.<p>

1.  To hell with Bash, give us kick instead.  Most SKs use 2H slash, and even with the additions of a few 1H slash weapons that are decent, we get double attack not dual wield.  Not to mention that the 2H slash has become a trademark SK weapon.  We look so damn evil weilding a big sword or axe.  Menacing.  So what we have is a bunch of humie/de/erudite SKs not using one of their skills that they're paying exp penalties for.  While some of you folks (trolls ogres) would say that we should play the big races for bash with 2H slash i disagree.  No race should really make a "better sk" than others, and with the current imbalance it leans toward Trolls and Ogres making better SKs (INT and mana issues aside)<p>

2.  Pets.  This has become a hot issue, and instead of changing the stats, why dont they have mobs treat your pet as the same level as you for aggro purposes.  Also as for look, while a shadowed image with glowing eyes (although it would look neat as hell) would require extra work, why not allow us pet ghouls?  You see ghoul guards in front of the DE lodge of dead, so why not have them as allies/pets?  Just change the "skin" and alter the aggro level and PRESTO! many SKs would be satisfied.<p>

3.  Harm Touch.  Once again a hot topic, but why not instead of changing damage, add an extra effect?  While we are the anathema to paladins, who says we have to be exact opposites?  Wouldnt playing an opposite but different, equaly deadly Dark Knight be more fun and original?  Dunno on exact effect, but why not have 50% dmg inflicted upon mob or whatever be channeled into you?  That way you can heal in an emergency while still doing our "deadly touch of hate"?  The pallys would not be less balanced, and our skill would be more interesting and would reflect upon our "theft like" spells.  We wouldnt be healers, we would be "vampires".  (see lifetap, siphon str, dark reaver etc.  there is a tendency for SK effects to hurt the opponent while aiding the dark knight)<p>

Conclusion.  None of these requests/wishlists have any real imbalancing effect.  Mostly theyre cosmetic and minor for the most part.  It would also require very little work out of Verant, and most of us SKs would just like a change.  We feel like we arent a true class, and need more distinguishing traits to make us feel better, and deadlier.  Verant, were not asking for a super class, just an independent one.<hr>"We all go a little crazy sometimes"<br>
           -Norman Bates</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
